data.title: Delicious pizza
data.text: Hadn't been here in years. Sure glad we stopped by.  Pizza was really tasty-delicious crust. Good service. Convenient location with plenty of parking.

data.title: Great lunch Great service.
data.text:
My family was running errands on the mainland and we took a chance on a pizza place we'd never been to as it was convenient.

Simply put, if we lived in Tamarac we'd be regulars.

We had a pizza, some wings and a cannoli for dessert.  Everything was very good and the prices were reasonable.

I'd also like to mention our server, Maria according to our receipt.  He was polite, engaging and efficient.  Thanks Maria!  ;-)  We'll be back if we're in the area again.

data.title: Our Favorite New Italian Place
data.text: I'm writing this review after several visits to At's A Pizza over two month's time.  We discovered this place very near our house back in July, 2016.  The first time we went we ordered pizza, garlic rolls, and ziti. What were we thinking!  That was a huge amount of food for two people, so we had a ton of leftovers.  Let me start with the pizza and qualify this by noting that pizza preferences are very subjective.  My brother and I both thought it was OK, but my brother thought the crust was too thin and tough and I thought the pie was too greasy. However, I can also see how someone else would just love that pizza, including a bunch of our friends.  And I have to qualify my statement further by saying that we ate every bite of it over the next day or so.  The ziti, however, was another story.  Oh.my.goodness!  It was SOOOOO good.  Truly the best ziti ever.  It's a huge plateful, with lots of cheese and wonderful sauce.  It's a winner for sure.  We'll be back for more of that.  Absolutely.  The next visit, I tried a Steak Philly, and that was also quite yummy.  And let me just pause here to say the staff are really nice people.  We really have enjoyed our brief conversations with them and feel welcome there.  Our next visits involved ziti again.  How could they not?  The staff rave about the fried cannolis, but we've always been too full to try them.  Maybe next time we'll start with dessert...

data.title: Two slices and a drink for $5
data.text:
Two slices and a drink $5 not bad considering today's economy. Just needs a facelift or  remodel interior other than that this was an excellent visit and I will return.
(Food Psychic)

data.title: Great Italian food
data.text: The food here is absolutely amazing. I have been coming here for about a year and the food never disappoints. I love their delicious pizza and their pasta is to die for! The lasagna is a must try. Service is always fast and the staff is excellent. I would recommend this place to anyone.

data.title: Local Italian Restaurant great for lunch or dinner
data.text:
A local favorite of my family is At's a Pizza

Food is cooked to order, and the pizza is very good.  Dinner portions are huge.

data.title: Our usual delivery place
data.text: This is our go-to spot for delivery, and has been for years.  The pizza, NY style, is consistently great, and we often get pasta or veal.  Eggplant Rollatini is my favorite, the wife likes Veal francese.  They both come with pasta, and you can request any of several sauces.  Garlic rolls with loads of extra garlic on request are a real delight!  They used to have somebody taking orders over the phone who had lost the will to live, but he's been gone (or replaced) with someone more courteous for quite a while.  Never really been disappointed

data.title: Dont eat here
data.text: My first time every ordering from them and they did not arrive until 1 and 45 minutes later because the person taking my order wrote my address down wrong. I ordered there again and the delivery boy named Eric was extremely rude, they have no  type of customer service skills. I ordered from twice and had an issue twice.

data.title: Offers pizza lunch specials
data.text: Food is good, attentive personnel. Located in a strip mall. We had the pizza lunch special for $5.50, which included two slices of pizza and a soft drink. They offer many Italian items. I understand this place is owned and ran by real Italians:)

data.title: Get the meats pie.
data.text: It's the only place with any consistency on University Drive. We've been ordering Pizza from this place for years and haven't got a bad one yet. Good garlic rolls also.

data.title: Very Good!  Small place in a strip mall
data.text: This is a small place, maybe 9 tables.  The food is basic Italian and pizza.  It is not fine dining, but the food is very good for the price you pay.   The do a good takeout business.  We went there for dinner at about 6:00pm.  They have early bird dinners that range from about $10 to $12.50.  The early bird dinners include soup, salad, goals, dessert, and coffee or tea.  I had the shrimp parmigiana, which came with spaghetti.  The shrimps were large, breaded, baked, and with cheese. The shrimp parmigiana special was the most expensive of the early bird dinners at $12.50.  It was a good solid meal.  The wife had the eggplant rollatini at $11.50.  We enjoyed our dinners and we would go back again.  They do have beer and wine.   Service was friendly.  Remember that this is not a fancy place and the price range indicates that.  But it is a wonderful place within its price range.  We did not have the pizza, but they looked good on the other tables.

data.title: Eh
data.text: Pizza was sub par. Not sure about south Florida pizza, but this can't be the best there is. Was not enjoyed by 5 of the 6 people.

data.title: BEST PIZZA!
data.text: Ever since I moved to Florida I've been looking for a non chain good pizza place and I found one!!! The WINGS are some of the BEST my hard to please husband has tasted and LOVED!!!! IF you have not ate at this place you are truly missing out!!!!

data.title: Holy Cow
data.text: From the moment you sit down, in this small restaurant,  you know all is truly italian. My meal was outstanding!  I ordered an antipasto, and manicotti. The sauce brought back memories of meals at my aunt bobbies house, in brooklyn. It tasted homemade. The garlic rolls were just delicious and the antipasto was.... You really have to experience  this place yourself!

data.title: Surprisingly good Pizza
data.text: We ordered a pizza for pickup. It is thin New York Style.  We ordered it with pepperoni and thought that it was a good product. Nicely spiced, and piping hot. We had to wait a few minutes after we got there for it to be ready.  The restaurant itself is very small, very basic, very cramped, and very noisy. I am guessing it was so busy because of the early bird specials, which seemed to be popular with the senior crowd.  Not sure that we would enjoy the dining experience.  May try a takeout dinner sometime. The early bird specials are not available for takeout. Crowded counter service with typical New York atmosphere and attitude.

data.title: Pizza and Italian entrees you'll return again and again for
data.text: This New york style pizza and entrees will have you coming back again and again. Their pizza is always fresh and has an excellent flavor. They are family owned and very freindly

data.title: Delicious and Great Service!
data.text:
I just ran a meetup group with ten of us attending at At's A Pizza.  It was my first  time there and all I can say is we all loved the food and our waiter was great at getting our food out quickly and getting our checks to us quickly as we requested them.  Sorry, can't remember the waiter's name but he really was nice and very sincerely thanked us ans invited us all to come back again soon).  Very classy for a casual and very reasonably priced neighborhood place.
My eggplant Parmesan was delicious and I, with my very healthy appetite, had enough left over to take home for dinner tomorrow night.
I will definitely be having another meetup there again in the near future!

data.title: Go to Ferros instead
data.text:
Owners are rude. This place has mostly seniors that have no taste buds left or can see the food 
They have been around over 30 years. Go down the street to sunflower shopping plaza

data.title: Typical New York Pizza
data.text:
Had a group of us working in the area so we all went for pizza. The service was very good. Waitress was fast and came back often. Pizzas came out fast. 

The pizza was good. Crust was thin and crispy, cook just right. All five of us liked it. Pizza was a little greasy, but for me it was the right amount.

data.title: The best pizza around
data.text: Don't live near but every so often will travel to get the most delis pizza around.  Been in business for over thirty years.  When near, stop in and enjoy!
